4. Applies an additional filter using `reaction::filter()` to only propagate actual status changes
5. Updates the sensor and records recomputation counts at each step
6. Returns the final status along with the recomputation counts after each update

The filter logic ensures that the status is only recomputed when the sensor value changes by more than the specified threshold, demonstrating how reactive computations can be conditionally triggered based on input changes.

